ke to get 2 clerics so that we are covered if Isli can't come and then Malduun can play who he wants.  We need nukers!  For support we need a chanter.<br>
<br>
I have thought long and hard about this and have come to the conclusion that IF the book does happen to drop at this one I'd like to reserve it. I'm sorry fellow paladins but hey what's the chance of that ACTUALLY happening?<br>
<br>
**ATTENTION CLERICS AND NECROMANCERS- Please bring any (and enough) dots to cover buffs, necromancers please carry a couple of coffins with you and have one in your bank in case we have people in the pits. At the end of the raid give me the bill for what was used and you will be reimbursed**<br>
<br>
Leader: Sadili<br>
Backup Leader: Singsang<br>
Where: Permafrost (Vox)<br>
Meeting Time: 10cst (8pst, 11est)pm<br>
Who: 40-52 main raid force, 53+ on support group.<br>
Goal: Kill Vox, get loot and HAVE FUN!<br>
Number of Groups: 4-5<br>
Level Range: Open 40+ with 45+ HIGHLY preferred (big difference on resists). One &quot;support group&quot; of 53+ desired to speed the raid along by clearing all mobs between raid force and Vox, plus buffs. Support DOES roll on loot<br>
Multiple Channels: <br>
VoxWeekly (Main raid channel. All raiders should join this channel, but only immediate raid business please)<br>
VoxHeal (Clerics and designated tanks only)<br>
VoxChat (All raiders, but this is the garbage channel. If you need to chit chat, do it here to keep the main channel clear).<br>
Alternative Goal: Just plain have fun folks.<br>
<br>
NOTES:<br>
<br>
As we move in, PAY ATTENTION! Vox' lair has pits around it - step only where you are told to. There will be a gatekeeper - do NOT go past them unless told to do so.<br>
Bring your best resist gear. MR of at least 50 and CR of at least 100 is HIGHLY desirable.<br>
Be prepared to be there 3-3.5 hours. In the unlikely case of wipeout, we will clean up and make a second attempt; otherwise, the support group should allow us to keep raid time to 2 hours or less even allowing for buffs.<br>
<br>
<br>
LOOT RULES:<br>
All cash loot held for reinbursement of buff components.<br>
NBG Folks, but still some loot to be had!<br>
<br>
<br>
Crystalline Spear: Open roll. <br>
Dragon Bone Bracelet: Open Melee roll for those that will actually use it.<br>
Kayruuls Mystic Pouch: Open Roll. <br>
McVaxius' Horn of War: Bard only for those that this would be an upgrade for.<br>
Runed Bolster Belt: Primary Melee Classes (War, Rng, SK, Pal, Monk, Rog, BL)<br>
Scimitar of the Mistwalker: Tough one. Probably open like the Crystalline spear, but this one is borerline, so DRU/RNG/BST speak up).<br>
Spell: Ice Comet: Wiz that doesn't have it yet<br>
Staff of Forbidden Rites: Open roll.<br>
Tobrin's Mystical Eyepatch: Casters<br>
Warhammer of Divine Grace: Clerics that will use it or open roll.<br>
White Dragon Hide (for white dragon hide cloak quest): Open. <br>
White Dragon Scales: Bard that doesn't have them. <br>
Torn Frost Covered Book: Reserved for this one.<br>
<br>
Please indicate whether you are PoP enabled when signing up - it makes a difference on what group I put you in, as we do use the raid feature with those we can.<br>
<br>
NOTE:There is a 15pp per person tithe to cover buff component costs. This is banked separately for continued use on these raids. <br>
<br>
PLANNED GROUP SET UP<br>
<br>
Group 1 (1 Tank, 2 Pally, 1 Bard, 2 Cleric)<br>
Judgen, 52 Warrior(Group Leader)<br>
Sapphyrre, 51 Paladin<br>
Deepaxe, 45 Paladin<br>
Singsang, 53 Bard(suicide)<br>
Isli, 47 Cleric (tentative)<br>
Malduun, 51 Cleric<br>
<br>
